STRATEGIC REASONING: {'Maximize my total importance under 3481 effort. Compute value/effort ratios and also total values. Items with highest importance: A04(780/461), A71(783/332), A87(668/553), C01(484/313), C54(461/359), A10(500/749), A03(508/736), B41(583/542), B32(389/409), B35(262/127), C17(138/777), B86(215/348), B33(97/802), A77(121/453), C00(65/1). Greedy by ratio suggests: C00(65), B35(262), A71(783), C01(484), A04(780), C54(461), B41(583), B86(215), B32(389), A87(668) checking effort sum feasibility. Let’s build: Start with A71(332), A04(461)->793, C01(313)->1106, C54(359)->1465, B41(542)->2007, A87(553)->2560, B32(409)->2969, B35(127)->3096, C00(1)->3097. Remaining limit 384. Add B86(348)->3445. Remaining 36 cannot add others. Total items: {A71,A04,C01,C54,B41,A87,B32,B35,C00,B86}. Effort sum: 332+461+313+359+542+553+409+127+1+348=3445 ≤ 3481. Value sum: 783+780+484+461+583+668+389+262+65+215=4,690. Check if swapping could improve: remaining capacity 36, items left A10(749) no, A03(736) no, C17(777) no, B33(802) no, A77(453) no. Consider replacing low-value B86(215,348) with something else: capacity would be 384+348=732; could we fit A03(736) no, A10(749) no, C17(777) no, A77(453) plus something small? 732 could fit A77(453) + maybe nothing else >279 like C00(1) already included. But we already have C00. If we remove B86 and add A77(453) we exceed by +105. What if remove B32(409,389) instead and keep B86? Free 409+36=445 could add A77(453) still 8 over. Replace B32(409) with A77(453) increases effort by 44 to 3489 > limit. Replace B35(127,262) with nothing yields spare 163, could we add something better than 262 within 163? None. Replace B86(215) with nothing frees 348, could we add something better within 384+? Already checked. What about include A10(500) by dropping some: Need 749 effort; free 36 short by 713; drop B86(348) leaves 384, still 365 short; drop B32(409) leaves 445, still 304 short; dropping both B86 and B32 frees 757 which fits A10. New set