00? cannot drop C00. Need more like plus B35(127) -> 920; importance change: -65-97-500 +780 = +118 net but we lose B35 high 500; worse. Add C17 instead: swap A04(461) + A71(332)=793 for C17(777) net importance +583-65-97=+421 and keeps effort fine. Compare with earlier simple swap A04->A77 gives +571 which is better. Could also swap A71(332,65) for something small effort high value? None small. Maybe swap B41(542,138) for A77(453,668): effort -89, importance +530 big; that seems even better and less likely opponent will drop B41? They wanted to keep B41 as core. But I can argue efficiency: A77 gives more bang per effort. So propose replacing B41 with A77 while keeping rest. Let's compute new set effort: 3445 -542 +453 = 3356 within limit. Total importance change +668-138 = +530; new total 4076. That is excellent for me. Opponent might resist losing B41. Offer alternative: swap A04 for A77 also works and keeps their stated core? They wanted to keep A04 as core too. They listed core: A71, A04, C01, C54, B41, A87. They are less willing to drop A04 or B41. But they mentioned flexibility on B86 or B32; for me B86(508) and B32(484) are valuable; I prefer to keep them. So I should first counter with small change: add A77 and remove A04 or B41; justify by improving balance and staying under limit. I’ll propose the swap B41->A77 as my preferred. If they resist, I can offer swapping A04->A77 as fallback. I must include ARGUMENT and a PROPOSAL. Also include REFUSE? I can just counter-propose without REFUSE. I won't agree yet.'}
